    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Not quite. It calls the enumerator of your object to enumerate it, and receives back a two element array for each item. It doesn't then enumerate each of those arrays, that would be an extra level of enumeration. ðŸ™‚ \r\n\r\nI would guess that somewhere in its logic it converts these either implicitly or explicitly to string, which presumably forces PS to call `ToString()` on the resulting array.",
